  "prompt": "You push backward against the ground to move a skateboard forward. The force you make acts against the ground. What force acts against you to move you forward?",
  "response": "When you push backward against the ground to move a skateboard forward, you are applying a force on the ground. According to Newton's Third Law of Motion, for every action, there is an equal and opposite reaction. \n\nIn this case, the action is you pushing the ground backward. The reaction force is the ground pushing you forward with an equal magnitude of force. This reaction force from the ground propels you and the skateboard forward. \n\nSo, to directly answer your question, the force that acts against you to move you forward is the reaction force from the ground, pushing in the opposite direction to your initial push.",
